Hello dear Herb!

Thank you so much for your note.  I'm very happy that we are in email touch=
.

I've been thinking of you and now what is our "shared" experience.  Nothing=
, but nothing could have prepared me.  I just cannot wrap my head around ho=
w FAST without a minute of warning that I lost Peter.  Exactly the way he a=
lways hoped that it would be,  but stunningly sad and sorrow filled for me =
and the family.  Almost two months now and it's a struggle. For so many rea=
sons,  and on so many levels and dimensions.  I know you understand.

Peter thought the world of you and Marion and we both enjoyed the time we s=
pent with you.  In fact,  you have been on his mind and on his short list o=
f people he most wanted to see.  We were planning to get thru his 80th BD c=
elebrations and then to connect with the people that we cared about the mos=
t.  You were at the top of the list.  I'm so sorry that we did not.  The ti=
ming of this just has me stunned and deeply saddened.  He was doing so well=
 and was SO happy.  That is truly a blessing.  Not a minute of suffering.  =
I was with him.

I have relocated back to Cleveland, where my frail and ailing Mother is jus=
t hanging on.  I cannot believe that I lost Peter before we lost Mom.  Agai=
n,  very difficult to wrap my head around.

My plan is to spend a good bit of time in NYC.  I would love to see you for=
 a hug and a hello if you have any plans to be in NYC and have the time,  p=
lease do let me know.

Thank you again for your kind words and for being in touch.

Hugs
Janet


