Thank you dear Susan for your thoughtful and heartfelt note.

It's only been 7 weeks today since Peter's funeral and I constantly struggl=
e to wrap my head around how FAST he left us,  not one second of warning.  =
A blessing for him,  and stunningly sad for me.  I am trying to stay ground=
ed in his strength and love.  Some days are a little lighter than others an=
d other days it is almost impossible to exhale.  I know you understand grie=
ving and loss.  It's tough for me to navigate my world without Peter.  But =
I am trying to make him proud of me.

Please give my best to your Dad and thank you so much for taking the time t=
o write.  Peter was always very impressed with you and held you in the high=
est regard.  I hope that our paths cross again someday, somewhere.

Take good care of yourself.

Hugs & Love,
Janet

